sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client / Dashboard
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Storage as Storage Backend<br/>(PVC/DB/MinIO)
    participant ModelMesh as ModelMesh<br/>Serving Runtime
    participant KServeIS as KServe<br/>InferenceService
    participant ModelServer as KServe/ModelMesh<br/>Model Server
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>OpenShift Monitoring
    participant MariaDB as MariaDB/MySQL<br/>3306/TCP JDBC

    Note over Client,Prometheus: Flow 1: Inference Payload Ingestion (ModelMesh → TrustyAI)
    ModelMesh->>TrustyAI: POST /consumer/kserve/v2<br/>HTTP 8080/TCP, No Auth
    TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: KServeInferencePayloadReconciler<br/>matches request ↔ response
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Persist observation data<br/>Filesystem/JDBC/HTTP

    Note over Client,Prometheus: Flow 2: CloudEvents Payload Ingestion (KServe → TrustyAI)
    KServeIS->>TrustyAI: CloudEvents (Knative trigger)<br/>org.kubeflow.serving.inference.*<br/>HTTP 8080/TCP
    TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: KServeInferencePayloadReconciler<br/>matches request ↔ response
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Persist observation data

    Note over Client,Prometheus: Flow 3: Fairness/Drift Metric Computation
    Client->>Route: POST /metrics/group/fairness/spd<br/>HTTP
    Route->>TrustyAI: Forward request<br/>HTTP 8080/TCP
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Read observation data<br/>Filesystem/JDBC
    Storage-->>TrustyAI: Observation dataset
    TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: Compute SPD/DIR metric
    TrustyAI-->>Route: Metric result (JSON)
    Route-->>Client: Metric result

    Note over TrustyAI,Prometheus: Scheduled Metric Publishing (every 5s default)
    loop PrometheusScheduler (@Scheduled)
        TrustyAI->>Storage: Read stored observations
        Storage-->>TrustyAI: Data
        TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: Compute all registered metrics<br/>Publish as Micrometer gauges<br/>(trustyai_spd, trustyai_dir)
    end
    Prometheus->>TrustyAI: GET /q/metrics<br/>HTTP 8080/TCP<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA)
    TrustyAI-->>Prometheus: Prometheus metrics<br/>(trustyai_spd, trustyai_dir, ...)

    Note over Client,Prometheus: Flow 4: Explainability Request (ODH only)
    Client->>Route: POST /explainers/local/lime<br/>HTTP
    Route->>TrustyAI: Forward request<br/>HTTP 8080/TCP
    TrustyAI->>ModelServer: KServe v2 HTTP inference<br/>HTTP 8080/TCP, No TLS
    ModelServer-->>TrustyAI: Prediction result
    TrustyAI->>ModelServer: KServe v2 gRPC inference<br/>gRPC, plaintext
    ModelServer-->>TrustyAI: Prediction result
    TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: LIME algorithm computation
    TrustyAI-->>Route: Explanation result (JSON)
    Route-->>Client: Explanation result

    Note over TrustyAI,MariaDB: Storage Backend Options
    alt PVC Storage Mode
        TrustyAI->>Storage: Read/Write CSV files<br/>at /inputs (PVC mount)
    else DATABASE Storage Mode
        TrustyAI->>MariaDB: JDBC queries<br/>3306/TCP, Username/Password
    else MINIO Storage Mode
        TrustyAI->>Storage: S3 API calls<br/>Access Key/Secret Key
    end
